History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient has been feeling overwhelmed by the pressure to create good writing and sometimes gets stuck on ideas. They have been trying to manage usual work stress and are working on letting go of past interactions, focusing on the present instead.
Psychosocial History: The patient enjoys deep conversations with friends and has received encouraging feedback on their writing projects, which has motivated them to write more. They practice mindfulness techniques like breathing exercises but are not consistent.
Physiological Observations: The patient finds swimming refreshing and beneficial for relieving stress, which helps improve their overall mood.
Current Functional Status: The patient is trying to set aside time each week to focus on writing, despite it being slow. They are managing work stress and maintaining a healthy perspective.
Therapeutic Interventions: The patient is encouraged to incorporate free-writing into their routine and practice mindfulness a few times a week.
Next Steps: The patient plans to free-write for ten minutes a day and practice mindfulness twice a week.
